#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an7.55:9.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, anupādāparinibbānaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is extinguishment by not grasping? "

msgctxt "an7.55:9.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ paṭipanno hoti: "
msgstr "Take a mendicant who practices like this: "

msgctxt "an7.55:9.3"
msgid "‘no cassa no ca me siyā, na bhavissati na me bhavissati, yadatthi yaṃ bhūtaṃ taṃ pajahāmī’ti upekkhaṃ paṭilabhati. "
msgstr "‘It might not be, and it might not be mine. It will not be, and it will not be mine. I am giving up what exists, what has come to be.’ They gain equanimity. "

msgctxt "an7.55:9.4"
msgid "So bhave na rajjati, sambhave na rajjati, atthuttari padaṃ santaṃ sammappaññāya passati. "
msgstr "They’re not attached to life, or to creating a new life. And they see with right wisdom that there is a peaceful state beyond. "

msgctxt "an7.55:9.5"
msgid "Tañca khvassa padaṃ sabbena sabbaṃ sacchikataṃ hoti, tassa sabbena sabbaṃ mānānusayo pahīno hoti, sabbena sabbaṃ bhavarāgānusayo pahīno hoti, sabbena sabbaṃ avijjānusayo pahīno hoti. "
msgstr "And they have totally realized that state. They’ve completely given up the underlying tendencies of conceit, attachment to life, and ignorance. "

msgctxt "an7.55:9.6"
msgid "So āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "They’ve realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. "

msgctxt "an7.55:9.7"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anupādāparinibbānaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called extinguishment by not grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.55:9.8"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, satta purisagatiyo anupādā ca parinibbānan”ti. "
msgstr "These are the seven places people are reborn, and extinguishment by not grasping.” "

